{"type":"text","timestamp":1778467636218,"sessionID":"ses_1eb17ff60ffeOJ9MpRqtcvbz5Z","part":{"id":"prt_e14ee6ff50016r6KTk0xX20cdC","messageID":"msg_e14ee6a370014YxRU5JvyAEskX","sessionID":"ses_1eb17ff60ffeOJ9MpRqtcvbz5Z","type":"text","text":"I've completed the work for issue #31295. Here's a summary:\n\n**New term created:** `p24 cargo receptor complex` (GO:7770070)\n\n**What was done:**\n1. Analyzed the issue and confirmed the requester (@ValWood) wants a new cellular component term for the p24 complex, a conserved hetero-oligomeric cargo receptor at ER exit sites.\n2. Performed background research and validated all provided PMIDs (PMID:19566487, PMID:26224213, PMID:27569046, PMID:32456004, PMID:34647572).\n3. Searched existing GO terms and found the appropriate parent (`GO:0062137 cargo receptor complex`) and location (`GO:0070971 endoplasmic reticulum exit site`), as well as the process relationship (`GO:0090110 COPII-coated vesicle cargo loading`).\n4. Followed the design pattern of the existing sibling `GO:0061852 retrograde cargo receptor complex, Golgi to ER`.\n5. Created the new term in `terms/GO_7770070.obo`, checked it in to `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`, performed basic syntax validation, and committed with a detailed message.\n6. Created `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md` and `PR_COMMENTS.md` for feedback.\n\n**Files changed:** `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` (+13 lines)\n\n**Term structure:**\n- `is_a: GO:0062137` cargo receptor complex\n- `relationship: part_of GO:0070971` endoplasmic reticulum exit site\n- `relationship: capable_of_part_of GO:0090110` COPII-coated vesicle cargo loading\n- synonym: `p24 complex` (EXACT)\n\nEverything is now ready for you to feed back to the originating issue and PR.","time":{"start":1778467631093,"end":1778467636217}}}
